OL,3,CConcerns remain over 'forever
OL,4,Cchemicals' despite 'fully compliant'
OL,5,Cwater supply
OL,7,FA new report says Jersey's drinking
OL,8,Fwater is "fully compliant" with
OL,9,FJersey, UK, and EU regulations - but
OL,10,Fcampaigners against PFAS say it needs
OL,11,Fto be removed completely from the
OL,12,Fisland's water supply.
OL,14,FJersey Water published its annual
OL,15,Fwater quality testing data, which
OL,16,Ffound the 'forever chemical' known as
OL,17,FPFAS is within safe limits.
