OL,3,CConcerns remain over 'forever
OL,4,Cchemicals' despite 'fully compliant'
OL,5,Cwater supply
OL,7,FThe utility conducted over 42,000
OL,8,Ftests on untreated and treated
OL,9,Fdrinking water between October 2023
OL,10,Fand September 2024.
OL,12,FThey were testing for 48 PFAS
OL,13,Fcompounds, pesticides, and nitrates.
OL,15,FOverall, the tests on drinking water
OL,16,Fachieved 99.95% compliance with
OL,17,Fregulatory standards set by Jersey,
OL,18,Fthe UK, and the EU.
