OL,3,CConcerns remain over 'forever
OL,4,Cchemicals' despite 'fully compliant'
OL,5,Cwater supply
OL,7,FWhile eight PFAS compounds were
OL,8,Fdetected, the average concentration of
OL,9,FPFAS in Jersey's drinking water is
OL,10,F0.032 micrograms per litre - below the
OL,11,FEU limit of 0.1.
OL,13,FBut campaigners say action is needed
OL,14,Fto purge PFAS from the water supply
OL,15,Fentirely.
OL,17,FPer- and poly-fluoroalkyl substances
OL,18,F(PFAS) - also known as 'forever
OL,19,Fchemicals' - are long-lasting
OL,20,Fcontaminants that can be found
OL,21,Fglobally.
