OL,3,CConcerns remain over 'forever
OL,4,Cchemicals' despite 'fully compliant'
OL,5,Cwater supply
OL,7,FPFAS was used in firefighting foam at
OL,8,FJersey Airport in the 1990s and leaked
OL,9,Finto some private boreholes, with
OL,10,Ftrace amounts also finding their way
OL,11,Finto the island's main water supply.
OL,13,FThe chemicals have since been linked
OL,14,Fto health conditions, including some
OL,15,Ftypes of cancer.
OL,17,FHead of Water Quality at Jersey Water,
OL,18,FJeanette Sheldon, says: "We're very
OL,19,Faware of the concerns about PFAS
OL,20,Faround the island.
