OL,3,CConcerns remain over 'forever
OL,4,Cchemicals' despite 'fully compliant'
OL,5,Cwater supply
OL,7,F"We do share those concerns and we're
OL,8,Fdoing everything we can to minimise
OL,9,FPFAS in drinking water."
OL,11,FCampaigners, such as Debbie Thorne,
OL,12,Fbelieve that PFAS needs to be
OL,13,Fcompletely filtered out of Jersey's
OL,14,Fwater system.
OL,16,FDebbie says: "What we'd like the
OL,17,Fgovernment to do is acknowledge that
OL,18,Fthe problem does actually exist
OL,19,Fbecause we have evidence of that.
